    rationale: "During robotic docking, the surgical technologist assists the bedside assistant in positioning the robotic arms over the patient and attaching the sterile EndoWrist instruments and camera to the robotic arms through the trocars. The surgical technologist must maintain sterile technique throughout the docking process, ensuring instrument tips and camera lenses are clean and properly seated. The surgeon operates from the console (not the bedside team), trocars are placed by the surgeon before docking, and the robotic system does not require procedural programming. The surgical technologist should also have conventional laparoscopic instruments immediately available in case of robotic malfunction requiring conversion to standard laparoscopic or open technique.",
    difficulty: 4,
    category: "Equipment & Technology",
    topic: "robotic surgery",
    regionScope: "BOTH",
