    rationale: "Bupivacaine (Marcaine) is a long-acting amide-type local anesthetic with onset of 5-10 minutes and duration of 4-8 hours (longer with epinephrine). Epinephrine is added as a vasoconstrictor to prolong the local anesthetic effect and reduce bleeding at the incision site. The surgical technologist must properly label the local anesthetic syringe (drug name, concentration) and announce the medication when passing it to the surgeon. Maximum dose of bupivacaine is 2.5 mg/kg without epinephrine, 3 mg/kg with epinephrine. Critical safety point: bupivacaine is cardiotoxic — accidental intravascular injection can cause refractory cardiac arrest. Bupivacaine should NEVER be used for intravenous regional anesthesia (Bier block).",
