    id: "st-1544",
    stem: "When setting up for a procedure requiring the use of a pneumatic tourniquet on the upper extremity, the correct tourniquet pressure for an adult arm is typically:",
    options: ["50-75 mmHg above the patient's systolic blood pressure, not exceeding 250 mmHg for the upper extremity", "300-450 mmHg regardless of the patient's blood pressure", "100 mmHg above diastolic pressure for all extremity procedures", "The maximum pressure the tourniquet can generate to ensure complete blood occlusion"],
