    id: "st-1552",
    stem: "During a vascular surgery procedure, the surgeon requests a Satinsky clamp. This instrument is primarily used for:",
    options: ["Partial occlusion of a blood vessel to allow side-clamping while maintaining distal blood flow", "Complete occlusion of the aorta during aneurysm repair", "Clamping the vena cava during hepatic surgery", "Retracting the mesentery during bowel resection"],
