    rationale: "Malignant hyperthermia (MH) is a life-threatening hypermetabolic crisis triggered by volatile anesthetic agents (sevoflurane, desflurane, isoflurane) or succinylcholine. The surgical technologist's immediate priority is to assist in removing the triggering agent and prepare dantrolene sodium (Dantrium) for IV administration — the only specific treatment for MH. Dantrolene must be reconstituted with sterile water (each vial requires 60 mL of sterile water, and multiple vials are needed — initial dose is 2.5 mg/kg). The surgical technologist should also anticipate: iced saline for wound and body cavity irrigation, rectal temperature probe, arterial blood gas supplies, and a code cart. The procedure should be concluded as rapidly as possible. An MH cart should be immediately available in every OR suite.",
