    id: "st-1555",
    stem: "The Spaulding classification system categorizes patient care items based on their risk of infection. A surgical instrument that enters sterile body tissue is classified as:",
    options: ["Critical item — requires sterilization", "Semi-critical item — requires high-level disinfection", "Non-critical item — requires low-level disinfection", "Environmental surface — requires routine cleaning"],
