    rationale: "AORN (Association of periOperative Registered Nurses) and ASHRAE guidelines recommend OR relative humidity between 20-60%. Low humidity (below 20%) increases static electricity, which can cause ignition of flammable anesthetic gases and create discomfort for personnel. High humidity (above 60%) promotes microbial growth, causes condensation on cold surfaces (which can compromise sterile packaging), and creates uncomfortable working conditions. OR temperature is maintained at 68-73°F (20-23°C) for most procedures, though it may be increased for pediatric patients and burn patients to prevent hypothermia. The HVAC system provides positive pressure air flow (minimum 15 air changes per hour with 3 fresh air changes) to prevent contamination from adjacent areas.",
