    stem: "The concept of 'breaking scrub' refers to:",
    options: ["Any action that causes the scrubbed team member to become contaminated, requiring re-gowning and re-gloving", "The initial surgical hand scrub performed before entering the operating room", "Removing gloves at the end of the procedure after the final count", "The pause between cases when the team removes their sterile attire"],
